# Chatbot Implementation Guidelines

## Core Functionality
- The chatbot should display a chat interface with messages
- Allow users to send messages
- Display bot responses
- Support basic customization through props

## Component Structure
- Create separate components for:
  1. ChatContainer (main component)
  2. MessageList (to display messages)
  3. MessageItem (individual message)
  4. InputArea (for user input)
  5. Header (optional chatbot header)

## Props Interface
- Design a clean, intuitive props interface
- Include options for:
  - Initial messages
  - Bot name/avatar
  - Custom styling options
  - Callback for message handling
  - Placeholder text

## State Management
- Use React hooks for state management
- Keep message history in state
- Track loading states for bot responses

## Styling
- Use SCSS modules with clear class names
- Create variables for common values
- Support theming through props
- Ensure mobile responsiveness

## Accessibility
- Ensure proper keyboard navigation
- Add appropriate ARIA attributes
- Support screen readers
- Maintain good color contrast
